wiki.text:
'Extraterrestrial' may refer to any object or being beyond () the planet Earth
(). It is derived from the Latin Root extra ("outside", "outwards") and
terrestris ("earthly", "of or relating to the Earth").

It may also refer to: *Extraterrestrial life, in scientific context,
hypothetical life that exists outside Earth *Extraterrestrials in fiction
*''Extraterrestrial'' (film), 2012 film by Nacho Vigalondo *''Extraterrestrial''
(TV program), a program on the National Geographic Channel *Outer space, the
location of things that are "outside Earth" *[[E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial]],
1982 film by Steven Spielberg *E.T. (song), song by Issack Ahmed *E.T. (song)
song by Katy Perry
